<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
		<p>
			A <code>ui:inputEmail</code> component represents an email input field, which is rendered as an HTML <code>input</code> tag of type <code>email</code>.
			To render the output from a <code>ui:inputEmail</code> component, use the <code>ui:outputEmail</code> component. 
		</p>
		<p>
			To provide a field label for accessibility, use the <code>label</code> attribute. You can hide the label from view by setting <code>labelPosition="hidden"</code> and still maintain accessibility.
			
    	</p>
	</aura:description>	
	<aura:example name="inputExample" ref="uiExamples:inputExample" label="Using ui:inputEmail">
    		This example shows how you can use <code>ui:inputEmail</code> to get user input.
    </aura:example>	
</aura:documentation>